\ms1 Opening Considerations
\s1 Greeting
\m 
\v 1 \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w*, apostle \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w will|strong="G2307"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* brother \w Timothy|strong="G5095"\w*,\f + \fr 1:1 \ft He acknowledges a junior partner.\f* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w church|strong="G1577"\w*\f + \fr 1:1 \ft Since there were probably several local congregations meeting in homes in Corinth, not to mention “throughout Achaia”, I have rendered “church”. Note that Paul obviously intended that his letter have a wide circulation. Rather than give up their copy, would not the congregation that received the ‘original’ set about making verified copies to distribute to other locales? (Such a procedure would give us the beginnings of a ‘majority text’ in that region from the start.)\f* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Corinth|strong="G2882"\w*, \w together|strong="G4862"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* saints \w throughout|strong="G1722"\w* Achaia:
\v 2 \w Grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w from|strong="G1515"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* Sovereign\f + \fr 1:2 \ft Where ‘Lord’ occurs without the definite article, as here, I usually render ‘Sovereign’; with either ‘the’ or ‘our’ I usually render ‘Lord’.\f* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.
\s1 Praise for deliverance
\p 
\v 3 \w All|strong="G3956"\w* praise \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w compassion|strong="G3628"\w*\f + \fr 1:3 \ft Literally, ‘the compassions’ or ‘the mercies’. I suppose the point to be that He is the Source of all genuine compassion (you won't get any from Satan).\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w encouragement|strong="G3874"\w*,
\v 4 \w who|strong="G3739"\w* encourages \w us|strong="G1519"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w affliction|strong="G2347"\w*, \w so|strong="G1519"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w may|strong="G1410"\w* \w be|strong="G1410"\w* \w able|strong="G1410"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w encourage|strong="G3870"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w whatever|strong="G3739"\w* \w affliction|strong="G2347"\w*, \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w means|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w encouragement|strong="G3874"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w ourselves|strong="G2249"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w encouraged|strong="G3870"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.\f + \fr 1:4 \ft One important reason God sends suffering our way is so that we can help others later.\f*
\v 5 \w Because|strong="G3754"\w* \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sufferings|strong="G3804"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* flow \w over|strong="G4052"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w us|strong="G1519"\w*,\f + \fr 1:5 \ft We get our share of suffering, we participate in Christ's sufferings—Colossians 1:24 and 1 Peter 4:13. Evidently for God's Kingdom to increase among men, as we continue to undo Satan's works in the world, we have to suffer.\f* \w so|strong="G3779"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w our|strong="G2532"\w* encouraging \w overflows|strong="G4052"\w*, \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.
\v 6 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w*, \w if|strong="G1535"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w afflicted|strong="G2346"\w*, \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w for|strong="G5228"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w sake|strong="G5228"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w encouragement|strong="G3874"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w deliverance|strong="G4991"\w*, \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w effective|strong="G1754"\w* \w for|strong="G5228"\w* \w enduring|strong="G5281"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w same|strong="G3739"\w* \w sufferings|strong="G3804"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w suffering|strong="G3958"\w*
\v 7 (yes, \w our|strong="G2532"\w* \w hope|strong="G1680"\w* \w concerning|strong="G5228"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* steadfast);\f + \fr 1:7 \ft I take it that he is affirming his confidence that they will not cave in under the suffering.\f* \w if|strong="G5613"\w* \w we|strong="G3754"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* encouraged, \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \it also\it* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sake|strong="G5228"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w encouragement|strong="G3874"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* deliverance, \w since|strong="G3754"\w* \w we|strong="G3754"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w share|strong="G2844"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w encouragement|strong="G3874"\w* \w just|strong="G5613"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w do|strong="G1492"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sufferings|strong="G3804"\w*.\f + \fr 1:7 \ft We cannot stop people from going through their share of suffering, but we can encourage them.\f*
\p 
\v 8 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w so|strong="G2532"\w*, brothers, \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w do|strong="G1096"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w want|strong="G2309"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* ignorance \w concerning|strong="G2596"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w affliction|strong="G2347"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w came|strong="G1096"\w* \w upon|strong="G1722"\w* \w us|strong="G2249"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Asia|strong="G3588"\w*: \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w under|strong="G1722"\w* extreme pressure, \w beyond|strong="G5228"\w* \w our|strong="G2532"\w* \w strength|strong="G1411"\w*, \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w despaired|strong="G1820"\w* \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w life|strong="G2198"\w*.
\v 9 Yes, \w we|strong="G2192"\w* \w ourselves|strong="G1438"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w had|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* sentence \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w* \w within|strong="G1722"\w* \w ourselves|strong="G1438"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w we|strong="G2192"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w place|strong="G1722"\w* \w confidence|strong="G3982"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w ourselves|strong="G1438"\w*, \w but|strong="G3361"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w raises|strong="G1453"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w*;\f + \fr 1:9 \ft If you look to the God who heals the sick, it is because you are sick; if you look to the God who raises the dead, it is because you are facing death. Paul evidently figured he had been pretty close.\f*
\v 10 \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w deliver|strong="G4506"\w* \w us|strong="G1519"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w deadly|strong="G2288"\w* peril, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w still|strong="G2089"\w* delivers; \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w trust|strong="G1679"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* keep \w on|strong="G1519"\w* delivering,
\v 11 \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* adding \w your|strong="G1223"\w* cooperation \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w prayer|strong="G1162"\w*,\f + \fr 1:11 \ft Prayer makes a difference.\f* \w on|strong="G1519"\w* \w our|strong="G2532"\w* \w behalf|strong="G5228"\w*; \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w thanks|strong="G2168"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w given|strong="G2168"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* \w persons|strong="G4383"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w gift|strong="G5486"\w* \w bestowed|strong="G1519"\w* \w on|strong="G1519"\w* \w us|strong="G1519"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w means|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w*, \w on|strong="G1519"\w* \w your|strong="G1223"\w* \w behalf|strong="G5228"\w*.\f + \fr 1:11 \ft They will get a return on their ‘investment’, the time they spent in prayer. Some 25% of the Greek manuscripts have ‘our behalf’, as in most versions.\f*
\s1 A change of plans
\p 
\v 12 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* boast: \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w testimony|strong="G3142"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w conscience|strong="G4893"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* conducted \w ourselves|strong="G2249"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* openness \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w godly|strong="G2316"\w* \w sincerity|strong="G1505"\w*, \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w fleshly|strong="G4559"\w* \w wisdom|strong="G4678"\w* \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w especially|strong="G4056"\w* \w toward|strong="G4314"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*.
\v 13 \w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w we|strong="G3739"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w write|strong="G1125"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w any|strong="G3756"\w* \w other|strong="G1161"\w* \w things|strong="G3739"\w* \w than|strong="G2228"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w can|strong="G1063"\w* \w read|strong="G1125"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w understand|strong="G1921"\w*;\f + \fr 1:13 \ft I take it that Paul is saying that he never writes with the intention of obfuscating an issue. That would be a good example for everyone to follow.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w hope|strong="G1679"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* keep \w on|strong="G1161"\w* understanding \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w end|strong="G5056"\w*
