\s1 About the first letter
\p 
\v 4 \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w wrote|strong="G1125"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w great|strong="G4183"\w* \w distress|strong="G2347"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w anguish|strong="G4928"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w heart|strong="G2588"\w*, \w with|strong="G1537"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* \w tears|strong="G1144"\w*, \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w should|strong="G3588"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w made|strong="G3076"\w* \w sorrowful|strong="G3076"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* greatness \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G1097"\w* love \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*.
\v 5 \w So|strong="G2443"\w*, \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w* \w has|strong="G5100"\w* \w caused|strong="G3076"\w* \w grief|strong="G3076"\w*, \w he|strong="G1161"\w* \w has|strong="G5100"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w much|strong="G1912"\w* \w grieved|strong="G3076"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w as|strong="G1161"\w* \w he|strong="G1161"\w* \w has|strong="G5100"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w of|strong="G5100"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w some|strong="G5100"\w* extent—\w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G3756"\w* \w too|strong="G1912"\w* ‘heavy’.
\v 6 \w This|strong="G3778"\w* \w punishment|strong="G2009"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* inflicted \w by|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w majority|strong="G4183"\w*\f + \fr 2:6 \ft Note that it is not necessary for ‘everyone’ to be in agreement with disciplinary action.\f* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w sufficient|strong="G2425"\w* \w to|strong="G3778"\w* \w such|strong="G5108"\w* \w a|strong="G5108"\w* \w one|strong="G5108"\w*,
\v 7 \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w now|strong="G2532"\w*, \w on|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G5108"\w* side, \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w should|strong="G3588"\w* \w forgive|strong="G5483"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w comfort|strong="G3870"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w overwhelmed|strong="G2666"\w* \w by|strong="G2532"\w* \w excessive|strong="G4053"\w* \w sorrow|strong="G3077"\w*.
\v 8 \w Therefore|strong="G1352"\w* \w I|strong="G1352"\w* \w urge|strong="G3870"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w reaffirm|strong="G2964"\w* \w your|strong="G3870"\w* love \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w him|strong="G3870"\w*.\f + \fr 2:8 \ft The purpose of the discipline was to restore, not destroy.\f*
\p 
\v 9 \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w wrote|strong="G1125"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w end|strong="G1519"\w*: \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w put|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w test|strong="G1382"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w see|strong="G1097"\w* \w whether|strong="G1487"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w obedient|strong="G5255"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w*.
\v 10 \w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w forgive|strong="G5483"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w too|strong="G2532"\w*; further, \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w forgiven|strong="G5483"\w* \w anything|strong="G5100"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w someone|strong="G5100"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* done \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w your|strong="G1223"\w* \w sakes|strong="G1223"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w presence|strong="G4383"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*,\f + \fr 2:10 \ft An interesting concept: Paul does the forgiving ‘in the presence of Christ’. He clearly believes that his forgiving, or otherwise, makes a difference. Well, he had ordered the disciplinary action, so it was appropriate for him to address the consequences.\f*
\v 11 \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w we|strong="G1063"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w be|strong="G3756"\w* exploited \w by|strong="G5259"\w* \w Satan|strong="G4567"\w*; \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w we|strong="G1063"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w ignorant|strong="G3361"\w* \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w his|strong="G3588"\w* intentions.\f + \fr 2:11 \ft Well, at least we shouldn't be, but how many Christians today really take the enemy seriously? Paul will refer to Satan by name several times.\f*
\s2 An afterthought
\p 
\v 12 \w Also|strong="G2532"\w*, \w upon|strong="G1519"\w* \w arriving|strong="G2064"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Troas|strong="G5174"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w door|strong="G2374"\w* \w having|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* opened \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* Sovereign,\f + \fr 2:12 \ft If it was the Lord who opened the door, was that not indicative of His will? So did he move on against that will?\f*
\v 13 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w had|strong="G2192"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w rest|strong="G2192"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w*, \w because|strong="G2192"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w did|strong="G3361"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w find|strong="G2147"\w* \w Titus|strong="G5103"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* brother; \w so|strong="G1519"\w* taking \w leave|strong="G1831"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w went|strong="G1831"\w* \w on|strong="G1519"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w Macedonia|strong="G3109"\w*.
\ms1 We have a glorious ministry
\s1 A fragrance of life
\p 
\v 14 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w thanks|strong="G5485"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w always|strong="G3842"\w* \w leads|strong="G2358"\w* \w us|strong="G2249"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w triumph|strong="G2358"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*,\f + \fr 2:14 \ft The title ‘Christ’ is usually accompanied by the definite article, ‘\nd the\nd* Christ’—we are not to forget what the title really means.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w us|strong="G2249"\w* spreads \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w fragrance|strong="G3744"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w knowledge|strong="G1108"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 2:14 \ft The antecedent of the pronoun could be either the Father or the Son, but in this context most likely refers to the Son—getting to know Him is in view.\f* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w place|strong="G5117"\w*.
\v 15 \w Because|strong="G3754"\w* \w we|strong="G3754"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* aroma \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w being|strong="G1510"\w* \w saved|strong="G4982"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w being|strong="G1510"\w* wasted\f + \fr 2:15 \ft We are accustomed to ‘perishing’. The verb here has a considerable semantic area and can be rendered—destroy, kill, deprive, void, lose, perish—depending on the context, but I believe the root idea is ‘waste’. The only way to fulfill the purpose for which you were created, to realize your potential, is to turn your life over to Jesus. The alternative is to waste your life, both now and forever. Of course the enemy works to make people think the opposite.\f*—
\v 16 \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* smell \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w*, \w while|strong="G1161"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w those|strong="G3778"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w fragrance|strong="G3744"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w life|strong="G2222"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w life|strong="G2222"\w*\f + \fr 2:16 \ft The Gospel of Christ represents both life and death: if you receive it, you get life; if you reject it, you get death. Naturally, those in rebellion against God do not enjoy being reminded that they have chosen death.\f*—\w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G5101"\w* \w adequate|strong="G2425"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w such|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w*?
\v 17 \w However|strong="G5613"\w*, \w we|strong="G1063"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w rest|strong="G1510"\w*\f + \fr 2:17 \ft The Greek manuscripts are about evenly divided between “the rest” and ‘the many’, but I follow the best line of transmission.\f* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* retail\f + \fr 2:17 \ft A retailer makes his living by buying goods wholesale and reselling them piecemeal, at a profit. In our day there is no lack of those who dole out their teaching, precisely with a view to getting more money out of it.\f* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w word|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*; \w rather|strong="G3756"\w*, \w we|strong="G1063"\w* \w speak|strong="G2980"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w sincerity|strong="G1505"\w*, \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w very|strong="G4183"\w* \w presence|strong="G2713"\w*.\f + \fr 2:17 \ft To be objectively aware that you are in God's presence does have a way of encouraging you to make the right choices!\f*
\c 3
\s2 An aside
\m 
\v 1 (\w Are|strong="G5613"\w* \w we|strong="G5613"\w* beginning \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w commend|strong="G4921"\w* \w ourselves|strong="G1438"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w*? \w Do|strong="G3361"\w* \w we|strong="G5613"\w* \w need|strong="G5535"\w*, \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w some|strong="G5100"\w* \w do|strong="G3361"\w*, \w letters|strong="G1992"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* recommendation \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*,\f + \fr 3:1 \ft Note that the early church used letters of introduction to help them in evaluating new arrivals.\f* \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w commendation|strong="G4956"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*?
\v 2 \w You|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w our|strong="G2532"\w* \w letter|strong="G1992"\w*, inscribed \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w our|strong="G2532"\w* \w hearts|strong="G2588"\w*, \w known|strong="G1097"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* read \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w men|strong="G3956"\w*;
\v 3 \w you|strong="G3754"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w manifestly|strong="G5319"\w* \w a|strong="G1722"\w* \w letter|strong="G1992"\w* \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, mediated \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w us|strong="G2249"\w*, \w written|strong="G1449"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w ink|strong="G3188"\w* \w but|strong="G2316"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w living|strong="G2198"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*,\f + \fr 3:3 \ft In some sense all of us are ‘letters’ that those around us read. To the extent that we invest in others, build into their lives, we contribute to their ‘letters’. Of course it is our lives that people see, not what is inscribed on the heart.\f* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w stone|strong="G3035"\w* \w tablets|strong="G4109"\w* \w but|strong="G2316"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* ‘\w tablets|strong="G4109"\w*’ \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w hearts|strong="G2588"\w* \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w flesh|strong="G4560"\w*.)
\s1 Competent ministers
\p 
\v 4 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w we|strong="G1161"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w such|strong="G5108"\w* \w confidence|strong="G4006"\w* \w before|strong="G4314"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w because|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*;
\v 5 \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w competent|strong="G2425"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w ourselves|strong="G1438"\w* \w to|strong="G3756"\w* \w reckon|strong="G3049"\w* \w anything|strong="G5100"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w being|strong="G1510"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w ourselves|strong="G1438"\w*, \w but|strong="G2316"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* competence \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*\f + \fr 3:5 \ft Competence is basic to everything that is done in this world; anything done by an incompetent will almost always be inferior. This is certainly true in the spiritual realm, where work done ‘in the flesh’ is poor work.\f*—
\v 6 \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w*, \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w has|strong="G3739"\w* \w made|strong="G2427"\w* \w us|strong="G2427"\w* competent \w as|strong="G1161"\w* \w ministers|strong="G1249"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w new|strong="G2537"\w* \w covenant|strong="G1242"\w*;\f + \fr 3:6 \ft Note that Paul is clearly aware that he is promoting a new covenant. The old covenant was characterized by “letter”, while the new is characterized by “Spirit” (or “spirit”).\f* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w letter|strong="G1121"\w* \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*, \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w letter|strong="G1121"\w* kills, \w while|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w gives|strong="G2227"\w* \w life|strong="G2227"\w*.\f + \fr 3:6 \ft I have capitalized ‘Spirit’, but ‘spirit’ is also true. The ‘spirit’ of a message has to do with its purpose, which should take into consideration the local context.\f*
\s1 A greater glory
\p 
\v 7 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w ministry|strong="G1248"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w*, \w engraved|strong="G1795"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w letters|strong="G1121"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w stones|strong="G3037"\w*, \w came|strong="G1096"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w*—\w so|strong="G1161"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w children|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w Israel|strong="G2474"\w* \w could|strong="G1410"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* gaze \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w face|strong="G4383"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w Moses|strong="G3475"\w* \w because|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w his|strong="G1223"\w* \w countenance|strong="G4383"\w* (\w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G1096"\w* \w fading|strong="G2673"\w*)—
