\v 4 \w Yes|strong="G1063"\w*, \w being|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* ‘\w tent|strong="G4636"\w*’ \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* burden, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w we|strong="G3739"\w* \w groan|strong="G4727"\w*—\w not|strong="G3756"\w* enough \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w want|strong="G2309"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* strip, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* really \w clothed|strong="G1902"\w*; \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w mortal|strong="G2349"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w swallowed|strong="G2666"\w* \w up|strong="G2666"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Life|strong="G2222"\w*.\f + \fr 5:4 \ft This paragraph relates only to the redeemed; only we have the prospect of improving our ‘clothing’. As for the lost, the mortal will be swallowed up by the Death, and they will be left naked (but not cease to exist).\f*
\p 
\v 5 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w it|strong="G1161"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w has|strong="G2316"\w* \w prepared|strong="G2716"\w* \w us|strong="G1325"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w very|strong="G3778"\w* purpose, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w also|strong="G1161"\w* \w has|strong="G2316"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w us|strong="G1325"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* down payment \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*.\f + \fr 5:5 \ft If you don't have the Holy Spirit, you don't have a ‘contract’. He is the down payment on ‘the Life’ (verse 4); eternal life being a quality of life, we can start living it down here.\f*
