\v 8 \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w*, \w we|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w confident|strong="G2292"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* preferring \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w away|strong="G1553"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w body|strong="G4983"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w at|strong="G4314"\w* \w home|strong="G1736"\w* \w with|strong="G4314"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*.\f + \fr 5:8 \ft Paul is talking about facing death with confidence, knowing it is the doorway to something much better than this life. Of course this only applies to those who belong to Sovereign Jesus.\f*
\v 9 Yes, \w that|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w why|strong="G1352"\w* \w we|strong="G2532"\w* \w make|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w our|strong="G2532"\w* aim (\w whether|strong="G1535"\w* \w at|strong="G2532"\w* \w home|strong="G1736"\w* \w or|strong="G1535"\w* \w away|strong="G1553"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w*) \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w well|strong="G2532"\w* \w pleasing|strong="G2101"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G2532"\w*.
\v 10 \w Because|strong="G1223"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w must|strong="G1163"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w be|strong="G1163"\w* exposed \w before|strong="G1715"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*'s Judgment Seat, \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w each|strong="G1538"\w* \w one|strong="G1538"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w receive|strong="G2865"\w* \w his|strong="G3956"\w* \w due|strong="G1163"\w* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w* \w he|strong="G3739"\w* \w did|strong="G3588"\w* \w while|strong="G3739"\w* \w in|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w body|strong="G4983"\w*, \w whether|strong="G1535"\w* \w good|strong="G3956"\w* \w or|strong="G1535"\w* \w bad|strong="G5337"\w*.\f + \fr 5:10 \ft If we are wise, like Paul, we will never forget the Accounting. He was ‘confident’ that upon leaving his physical body he would be at home with the Lord. To have the same confidence we also must consciously live so as to be well pleasing to Him. Notice that the emphasis is on what we \bd \nd do\nd*\bd*.\f*
\v 11 \w Therefore|strong="G3767"\w*, \w since|strong="G1161"\w* \w we|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*'\w s|strong="G2962"\w* \w intimidation|strong="G5401"\w*,\f + \fr 5:11 \ft God's holiness is an aggressive quality that attacks anything evil that tries to approach. That holiness is truly intimidating, and we will all be judged by it. Jonathan Edwards preached on that basis, with extraordinary effect, but there are few in our day who follow his example. On a lower level, worldly people tend to feel uncomfortable in the presence of someone who is holy, sometimes to the point of reacting aggressively. As Satan increases his hold on the world, such aggressive reaction will become ever more common.\f* \w we|strong="G2532"\w* try \w to|strong="G2532"\w* convince \w people|strong="G1492"\w*.
\s1 Why \w Christ|strong="G2962"\w* \w died|strong="G3588"\w*
\p \w We|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w well|strong="G2532"\w* \w known|strong="G5319"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w hope|strong="G1679"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G2962"\w* \w consciences|strong="G4893"\w* \w as|strong="G1722"\w* \w well|strong="G2532"\w*.
