\v 15 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w died|strong="G3588"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \it now\it* \w live|strong="G2198"\w* \w should|strong="G3588"\w* \w no|strong="G3371"\w* \w longer|strong="G3371"\w* \w live|strong="G2198"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w themselves|strong="G1438"\w* \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w One|strong="G1520"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w died|strong="G3588"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*\f + \fr 5:15 \ft I follow the best line of transmission, along with a minority of the manuscript total (35% here), in reading “all” instead of the familiar ‘them’.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w raised|strong="G1453"\w* \w again|strong="G1453"\w*.\f + \fr 5:15 \ft The clearest statements giving \bd why\bd* Christ died begin with Romans 14:9, “that He might be \nd Lord\nd* of both the dead and the living”; followed by this verse, that we should no longer live for ourselves, but for \nd Him\nd*. Philippians 2:8-11 refers to the final victory. Hebrews 2:14 refers to destroying Satan; saving us from hell is a by-product. As it says in Romans 10:9, “if you confess with your mouth, ‘Jesus is Lord…’, you will be saved”.\f*
\s1 We are Christ's ambassadors
\p 
\v 16 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w*, \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w now|strong="G3568"\w* \w on|strong="G2596"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* regard \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w fleshly|strong="G4561"\w* perspective—\w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* ‘\w known|strong="G1097"\w*’ \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w in|strong="G2596"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w way|strong="G2596"\w*, \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w do|strong="G1492"\w* \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w longer|strong="G3765"\w*\f + \fr 5:16 \ft The unregenerate are forever trying to explain or understand Jesus in purely humanistic terms. We who are in Christ must not do so. Further, we should not try to understand anyone in such terms—we need to take account of what is happening in the spiritual realm. (As a student Saul of Tarsus had certainly seen and heard Jesus.)\f*—
\v 17 \w so|strong="G5620"\w* \w then|strong="G5620"\w*, \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w he|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w new|strong="G2537"\w* \w creation|strong="G2937"\w*; \w the|strong="G1722"\w* old \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w have|strong="G1096"\w* \w passed|strong="G3588"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w*; \w look|strong="G2400"\w*, \w all|strong="G1722"\w* \w has|strong="G1096"\w* \w become|strong="G1096"\w* \w new|strong="G2537"\w*!\f + \fr 5:17 \ft This is neither immediate nor automatic; it is potential. No benefit of the shed blood of God's Lamb is automatic; it must be appropriated.\f*
\v 18 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* ‘\w all|strong="G3956"\w*’ \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w has|strong="G2316"\w* \w reconciled|strong="G2644"\w* \w us|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Himself|strong="G1438"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2532"\w*\f + \fr 5:18 \ft Perhaps 3% of the Greek manuscripts omit “Jesus”, to be followed by NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.\f* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w us|strong="G1325"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w ministry|strong="G1248"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w reconciliation|strong="G2643"\w*,\f + \fr 5:18 \ft Yes, \nd the\nd* reconciliation—no other reconciling compares with reconciling men to God.\f*
\v 19 \w namely|strong="G5613"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w reconciling|strong="G2644"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Himself|strong="G1438"\w*,\f + \fr 5:19 \ft Wonderful, wonderful, wonderful!\f* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w imputing|strong="G3049"\w* \w their|strong="G1438"\w* \w trespasses|strong="G3900"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, \w including|strong="G2532"\w* committing \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w us|strong="G2249"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w message|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w reconciliation|strong="G2643"\w*.
\p 
\v 20 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w*, \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*'s \w ambassadors|strong="G4243"\w*, \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w though|strong="G5613"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w making|strong="G1189"\w* \w His|strong="G1223"\w* \w appeal|strong="G3870"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w us|strong="G2249"\w*. \w We|strong="G2249"\w* \w implore|strong="G3870"\w* \w you|strong="G5613"\w* \w on|strong="G5228"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*'s \w behalf|strong="G5228"\w*: \w Be|strong="G2316"\w* \w reconciled|strong="G2644"\w* \w to|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*!
\v 21 \w Because|strong="G1722"\w* \w He|strong="G3588"\w* \w made|strong="G4160"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w did|strong="G4160"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* sin \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* sin \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w behalf|strong="G5228"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w might|strong="G2316"\w* \w become|strong="G1096"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w righteousness|strong="G1343"\w*.\f + \fr 5:21 \ft Here we are face to face with the mystery of our redemption. Jesus, God's Son, never sinned, did not ‘know’ sin, experientially, but He was “made to be sin” on our behalf. It is a grim picture, as though on the cross He was changed into a bundle of sin. And in exchange He gave us His righteousness. How can we ‘measure’ or understand such love? It is beyond our comprehension. As Romans 11:33 expresses it: “Oh the depth of the riches of the wisdom and knowledge of God! How unsearchable are His judgments and His ways past finding out!”\f*
\c 6
\m 
\v 1 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w working|strong="G4903"\w* \w together|strong="G4903"\w*\f + \fr 6:1 \ft ‘Working together’ with whom? Presumably with other ambassadors, but also with God.\f* \w we|strong="G2532"\w* really \w urge|strong="G3870"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w receive|strong="G1209"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w vain|strong="G2756"\w*,
