\v 4 \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w begged|strong="G1189"\w* \w us|strong="G1519"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w much|strong="G4183"\w* entreaty \w to|strong="G1519"\w* receive \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w gift|strong="G5485"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sharing|strong="G2842"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w ministry|strong="G1248"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* saints
\v 5 —\w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w more|strong="G2532"\w* \w than|strong="G2532"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w hoped|strong="G1679"\w*, \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w* \w gave|strong="G1325"\w* \w themselves|strong="G1438"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*\f + \fr 8:5 \ft Is obeying the commands of Christ the exclusive privilege of the rich? How about the first believers, there in Jerusalem, were they rich or poor? It would appear that the vast majority were poor; so much so that the few well-to-do were selling their property to feed the rest. (That is what gave rise to the case of Ananias and Sapphira [Acts 4:32-5:11].) They evidently did not want to leave Jerusalem, in spite of the Lord's words recorded in Luke 24:49 and Acts 1:8. So God Himself sent the persecutions to disperse them. And they scattered, preaching as they went, poor though they were.\fp Here in 2 Corinthians 8:1-5 we find an account that is very much to the point. Those Macedonian believers were very poor (“extreme poverty”). Furthermore, they were experiencing a “severe test of affliction”. Even so, they insisted on giving. From verse 4 it almost seems that Paul felt a bit embarrassed about asking them to give—they needed help themselves! But they insisted; they wanted to give. And they gave more than they properly could (“beyond their ability”). But how was that possible? They had the mentality of the Kingdom—in verse 5 we read that “\bd first\bd* they gave themselves to the Lord”. And they must have understood the secret of God's economy, as described in 2 Corinthians 9:8.\f* (\w and|strong="G2532"\w* due \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'\w s|strong="G2962"\w* \w will|strong="G2307"\w*, \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w us|strong="G1325"\w*).
\p 
