\v 13 \w Such|strong="G5108"\w* \w men|strong="G5108"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* really \w false|strong="G5570"\w* \w apostles|strong="G5570"\w*, \w deceitful|strong="G1386"\w* \w workers|strong="G2040"\w*, transforming \w themselves|strong="G1519"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* ‘\w apostles|strong="G5570"\w*’ \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.\f + \fr 11:13 \ft There have always been those who want to ‘get on the bandwagon’, to get a free ride; who traffic in spiritual things for personal, temporal advantage. Since such people only do damage, Paul's desire to expose them stems from his concern for the Corinthians' welfare.\f*
\v 14 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w wonder|strong="G2295"\w*, \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w Satan|strong="G4567"\w* \w himself|strong="G1519"\w* masquerades \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w an|strong="G2532"\w* angel \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w light|strong="G5457"\w*.
