\v 4 \w how|strong="G3754"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* caught \w up|strong="G1519"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w Paradise|strong="G3857"\w*\f + \fr 12:4 \ft “Paradise” here evidently refers to Heaven. In Luke 23:43 it refers to the half of Hades (Sheol in the OT) that was reserved for the righteous dead.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* heard inexpressible \w things|strong="G3588"\w*, \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w man|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w permitted|strong="G1832"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w tell|strong="G2980"\w*.
