\v 20 \w Yes|strong="G1063"\w*, \w I|strong="G2504"\w* \w am|strong="G2309"\w* \w afraid|strong="G5399"\w* \w that|strong="G3361"\w* \w when|strong="G2064"\w* \w I|strong="G2504"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w I|strong="G2504"\w* \w may|strong="G2504"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w find|strong="G2147"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w such|strong="G3634"\w* \w as|strong="G3634"\w* \w I|strong="G2504"\w* \w wish|strong="G2309"\w*, \w and|strong="G2064"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w find|strong="G2147"\w* \w me|strong="G2504"\w* \w such|strong="G3634"\w* \w as|strong="G3634"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w wish|strong="G2309"\w*—\w may|strong="G2504"\w* \w there|strong="G1063"\w* \w be|strong="G3756"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w strife|strong="G2054"\w*, jealousies, \w outbursts|strong="G2372"\w* \w of|strong="G2372"\w* \w anger|strong="G2372"\w*, factions, \w slanders|strong="G2636"\w*, gossipings, conceits, disorders—
\v 21 \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w when|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w humble|strong="G5013"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w before|strong="G1909"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w mourn|strong="G3996"\w* \w for|strong="G1909"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* previously \w sinned|strong="G4258"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w repented|strong="G3340"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* impurity \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w fornication|strong="G4202"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* licentiousness \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w practiced|strong="G4238"\w*.\f + \fr 12:21 \ft There is only one definite article for the three nouns, and ‘which’ is singular, so the three are regarded as a single ‘package’. Unfortunately there have always been, and continue to be, those who go back to a sinful lifestyle, and stay there. Like Paul, about all we can do for such is ‘mourn’.\f*
\c 13
\s2 I will not spare
\m 
\v 1 \w This|strong="G3778"\w* \w is|strong="G3778"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w third|strong="G5154"\w* \w time|strong="G5154"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G2532"\w* \w coming|strong="G2064"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*. “\w At|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w two|strong="G1417"\w* \w or|strong="G2532"\w* \w three|strong="G5140"\w* \w witnesses|strong="G3144"\w* \w shall|strong="G2532"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w word|strong="G4487"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w established|strong="G2476"\w*.”\f + \fr 13:1 \ft See Deuteronomy 19:15. It almost seems that Paul is comparing his visits to witnesses.\f*
\v 2 \w As|strong="G5613"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w already|strong="G4258"\w* \w said|strong="G2532"\w* \w while|strong="G5613"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G1437"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w second|strong="G1208"\w* \w time|strong="G1208"\w*, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w now|strong="G3568"\w* repeat \w in|strong="G1519"\w* writing\f + \fr 13:2 \ft Perhaps 3% of the Greek manuscripts omit “in writing”, to be followed by NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.\f* \w while|strong="G5613"\w* absent, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w sinned|strong="G4258"\w* \w before|strong="G1519"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w rest|strong="G3062"\w*: \w If|strong="G1437"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w spare|strong="G5339"\w*,
\v 3 \w since|strong="G1893"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w want|strong="G2212"\w* \w proof|strong="G1382"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w speaking|strong="G2980"\w* \w through|strong="G1722"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*—\w He|strong="G3739"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* weak \w toward|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w but|strong="G3588"\w* powerful \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*
\v 4 (\w although|strong="G5210"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G2532"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4717"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* weakness, \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w lives|strong="G2198"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w power|strong="G1411"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*). \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G2532"\w* weak \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Him|strong="G2532"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w live|strong="G2198"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w Him|strong="G2532"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w power|strong="G1411"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w toward|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*.\f + \fr 13:4 \ft Being weak in God's presence is one thing; being weak in our work for Him is quite another. I take Paul to be saying that being weak in God's presence triggers the outflow of His power in our work.\f*
\s2 Examine yourselves
\p 
\v 5 \w Examine|strong="G1381"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G1438"\w* \w as|strong="G1722"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* \w whether|strong="G1487"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*; \w test|strong="G3985"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G1438"\w*. \w Do|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G1438"\w* really \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w know|strong="G1921"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*?\f + \fr 13:5 \ft Sin does have a way of undermining confidence. A Christian who keeps on sinning tends to become less and less sure of his salvation.\f*—\w unless|strong="G1487"\w* \w indeed|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* disqualified.
